<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Malhaeth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I posted something about this on the clerics board at everlore, and didn't get a lot of well-reasoned responses. I have a very young dark elf cleric, and I'm wondering if it is worth keeping my 2hb skill going. Am I ever going to run into a 2hb weapon that is so exciting, I want to give up the AC and stat buffs of a shield?<P>I got one response that said no, just stick with 1hb, and others that were basically "2hb does more damage, so use it!" I figure damage-dealing isn't really my bag. So the question really boils down to: "is there a 2hb weapon with such great statt buffs that it will be better than shield and 1hb?"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trilvan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not that I have seen but I am sure there are others out there that are more well informed than I. <P>Currently I use a springwood club and the 18 wis idol. I cannot find any 2 hb that would match the 23 points of wisdom I get from this combo.<P>------------------<BR>Trilvan Lostheart<BR>46th Cleric of Love Peace and Happiness</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Not really.  But every now and then you might run across something that is fun to use and it would stink to not have the skill to use it.<P>I was messing around with a warrior friend in CT the other night (he was looking to stock up on Cazic gate potions).  He had a poison wind censor? 2hb weapon with a AE proc of rain of poison and that was a fun thing to do.<P>Had a couple pieces of equipment with me that added poison resist and then just buffed myself with Resist Poison and had a blast.  Got it to proc quite a bit.<P>But in everyday situations, there probably isn't much need to have maxed your 2hb skills.  If you are like the majority of us, you just want to have your skills maxed for the sake of it.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>59th Dwarven Templar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nornric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">From a Level 55 Perspective, without his Epic.<P>Yes and No! hehe with my current equipment my wis is 203 without and +wis items in either hand. I have a sarnak Battle sheild for Resists and my staff from my epic for one handed blunt purposes. Having just maxed out my 1HB a few weeks ago. I borrowed a NICE 2HB stick from a warrior in the guild to max out my 2HB. I am not doing so for Effencieny so much as just something I want to do. <P>Idealy since our Epic is 1HB that is the one you want to max out. If you want to have a little fun sure go ahead and Max out 2HB too.<P>Nornric<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I currently wield a 2hb over my epic now.  <P>Apothic Shissar Staff<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Panteroo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sorry to go off subject.. <P>but a +18 wis idol? OMG<P>what idol is this? I too have a SW club, but i still carry around my CGS (+9wis)...<P>and is it attainable at level 45?<P>Panteroo "totally drooling over the thought of an 18wis idol" Mcgillakudy</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">He's talking about the pearl kedge totem. For us mere mortals, there's no reason at all to waste time with 2hb. I got mine up to 130 or so just for kicks but it never did me any good. Poison Wind Censer is one of the enchanterbane line of weapons (AE procs) and can cause you to spend unnatural amounts of time without clarity.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Erm... Arturo... what's so great about the Apothic Shissar Staff that you would wield it in preference to epic + uber shield slot item? 2hb 26/52 9 STA 18 WIS 10 POI vs. 20/32 1hb 10 STA 25 WIS 15 CHA 10 Save all 100 mana... epic has better stats in every category, even weight. Is this a sentimental choice?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">*grins evily*<P>You forgot to list the effect on my staff.<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I carry a Springwood Club and Charred Guardian Shield as well. The Pearl Kedge Totem drops off a named goblin (Bildge Farfathom if I remember correctly) in Dagnor's Cauldron (that lake zone between Butcherblock and Unrest). It is +18wis, -9str   and VERY rare. The Paw of Opella is easier to get (though by no means easy in itself), provides 9A, 5Sta, 9Agi, 9Wis, -5Cha, -5vs Disease. Seems to me that unless you NEED that extra 9AGI, stick with the CGS until you can afford to lose the WIS altogether and get a high AC/Resist shield.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sorry yes it's Greater Healing. Is it a proc or an right-click effect?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">right click<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sounds very interesting... what's cast time? Do you ever equip epic/shield and just swap it in for the effect? Is it equipped only to use? Not that I will ever see one but I am interested in why you give up so much in stats/ac/resists for it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">dusklar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I maxed both mine out for a few reasons.. First off I got a staff of the waterwalker in Seb, and did not have an item that gave me enduring breath, and it was 2hb, and decent damage to delay, and I did not have my epic yet, so I wanted to use it for the enduring breath, the damage, and the wisdom increase.  I only lost the ac from not having the shield, but with shammie buffs, I could hit 70 damage or so, which I didnt think was bad for a pos high elf.  <BR>Secondly I figured that IF I would not get my epic, that down the road Verant may introduce another weapon that could be 2hb, and I would have to start my training on it at a later date. <BR>Lastly, it was fun to work on a skill for awhile, and to melee once and a great while instead of sitting and healing, sitting, etc. <BR>Practically though for me and the equip. that I have ran into, and if you want to choose, then I would recommend maxing 1hb with shield first.  Work on the 2hb for fun and possible later use.  Any 2hb weapons out there will more and likely be at the high end of the game, and you will have some time to work on it as you progress thru the levels.   Dusklar 59th cleric.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Personelly I like 1hs.<P>I got me a heretics sword or whatever and I look cool in barney swinging it at the monster.<P>To quote minsc and boo<P>"Evil meet sword, SWORD MEET EVIL!"<P>damage 2 delay 30 doesn't really affect the amount of damage I do as I can't hit squat even with offence and 1h blunt maxed anyhow :></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
